<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  tal:define="siteName python:view.siteInfo.get_name()">
  <tal:block metal:use-macro="context/@@groupserver_site_home_layout/page">
    <head>
      <title metal:fill-slot="title">
        Page Not Found (404):
        <tal:block replace="siteName"/>
      </title>
      
      <tal:block metal:fill-slot="metadata">
        <meta name="author" content="OnlineGroups.Net" />
        <meta name="description" content="Page not found page" />
      </tal:block>
      
    </head>
    <body>
      <div metal:fill-slot="externallinks" />
      <div metal:fill-slot="sitenavigation" id="sitenavigation">
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="/">Home</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div metal:fill-slot="contextnavigation" />
      <div metal:fill-slot="breadcrumb" />
      <div metal:fill-slot="footer"/>
      
      <div metal:fill-slot="body"
        tal:define="siteId view/siteInfo/id;
          gse python:modules['Products.XWFCore.XWFUtils'].get_support_email;
          supportEmail python:gse(context,siteId);">
        <h1>Page Not Found</h1>

        <!--Appologise, and state what went wrong -->
        <p id="appology">Sorry, the page you were trying to get to 
          <code class="url" tal:content="view/requested">http://some.site</code>
          could not be found.</p>
        <!-- Give a detailed explanation about what went wrong, and -->
        <!--   what can be done.-->
        <div id="user" tal:condition="python:view.problem == view.user">
          <p>A couple of things could have gone wrong.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>If you <strong>typed</strong> the address into the browser
              check the address to make sure the are no mistakes in 
              it.
              You will have to retype the address if there are any 
              mistakes.</li>
            <li>If you clicked on a link in an <strong>email</strong> check
              that the link is not split over multiple lines. 
              If it is you will have to correct it to ensure it is not
              split over multiple lines.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>If you are still having trouble 
            <a href="#" 
              tal:define="m string:Hi! I went to the address ${view/requested} and I saw a Page Not Found (404) error. I want to see... I found the link in...;
            msg python:view.quote(m)"
              tal:attributes="href string:mailto:${supportEmail}?Subject=Broken%20Address&amp;body=${msg}">email
                support</a> 
            with the specifics of your problem, and we will see what we
            can do to help. 
          </p>
        </div><!--user-->
        <p id="search" tal:condition="python:view.problem == view.search">
          The <strong>search results</strong> that you used contained a
          link to a page that does not exist.
          Hopefully this problem will be automatically fixed by the 
          search system.  
        </p><!--search-->
        <p id="external" 
          tal:condition="python:view.problem == view.external">
          The link you followed went to this site, but the specific page
          could not be found.
          The person who wrote 
          <a tal:attributes="href view/referer" href="#">the page you were
            on</a>
          may be able to correct the link.  
        </p><!--external-->
        <p id="internal" tal:condition="python:view.problem==view.internal"
          tal:define="m string:Hi! The link I followed from ${view/referer} to ${view/requested} was broken and I saw a Page Not Found (404) error.;
            msg python:view.quote(m)">
          <strong>We made a mistake</strong> so the link that you followed
          did not go where it should.
          The system has automatically made a note of our error, but if 
          you 
          <a href="#" title="Email support on this site"
            tal:attributes="href string:mailto:${supportEmail}?Subject=Broken%20Link&amp;body=${msg}"
            class="email">contact us</a> 
          we will get back to you when the link is fixed.
        </p><!--internal-->
        <!--Lastly, give the technical details about the error. Bots may-->
        <!--find this useful.-->
        <p id="technical">If you want to get all technical about it, 
          <code>404 Not Found</code>. 
          Make of that what you will. 
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
  </tal:block>
</html>

